[1] Minks, culled
Date: Mon 8 Jun 2020
Source: Boerderij [in Dutch, trans., edited]
https://www.boerderij.nl/Home/Nieuws/2020/6/Ruimen-nertsenbedrijven-gaat-hele-week-duren-594632E/


The culling of minks on 10 farms where infections with the coronavirus have been diagnosed, will take the whole week. Last [Sat 6 Jun 2020], all minks were killed on a farm in Deurne. On Sunday [7 Jun 2020], the animals were killed on 3 additional farms; the operation has been continued during [Mon 8 Jun 2020].

A total of 10 companies are involved and the NVWA [Dutch Food and Consumer Product Safety Authority] expects to complete the operation this week, according to a spokesman. The 1st company involved 1600 dams with an average of 5 young minks (puppies). The animals are killed on the farm and then transported to a rendering facility.

The NVWA will provide the details of the locations of the companies involved and the number of culled animals only after all the culling operations have been completed. The pelts of the animals are also destroyed and not used for clothing as is normally the case.

